**Content approach and weaknesses:** Top competitors (BTArtbox, L'Oréal Paris, OPI, Nailstrending.com) all cover colours and basic "do/avoid" lists. OPI frames by role type (creative, planner, leader) but skews toward product push. L'Oréal covers prep steps but is dated (2019). None address the emotional layer — the anxiety, the "is this too much" spiral — or give 2026-specific guidance tied to milky/soap nail trends. Most treat this as a simple colour list, not a decision framework.

**Visual patterns:** 6–10 images typical. Most use flat lay product shots or generic stock hand images. Opportunity to use real inspo-style hand photography by nail type and industry.

**Recommended image count:** 10–12. One visual anchor per major colour/industry section elevates this from a text list to a genuine inspo-plus-guidance hybrid.

### Competitor Gaps
**Unanswered audience questions:**
- "I have a second-round interview — do I need to change my nails from what I wore before?"
