**Missing semantic territory:**
- 2026 trend relevance (milky nails, soap nails, modern French) never appears in competitor articles
- Confidence psychology angle barely addressed
- Video/remote interview specific nail advice absent
- "What if I have no time" last-minute angle not covered
- Industry-specific quick-reference rarely done in one clear table or structure

**Audience blind spots:**
- People want a decision framework, not just a list — "yes/no by industry" structure is what they'd actually use
- Gen Z job seekers specifically are asking about nails they already have (bold, art, chrome) and whether to remove them
- The "chipped nail" fear is a bigger anxiety driver than colour choice — competitors don't address this emotional undercurrent

